cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper presents a method for combining model-free and model-based approaches in reinforcement learning, which is a topic that falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), robotics (cs.RO), control systems (cs.SY), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper specifically focuses on using Model Predictive Control (MPC) as a differentiable policy class, which is a technique that is commonly used in control systems and robotics research (cs.RO, cs.SY), but also involves differentiating through a convex approximation using KKT conditions, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.RO, and cs.SY, followed by cs.AI and cs.NE.
